wiki-base is an independent baseline (not a fork), built on publicly shared ideas
and prior art. The MIT License applies to the original files in this repository.
Attribution to the work it builds on:

- The "LLM Wiki" idea — compile a persistent, compounding markdown knowledge base
  once and keep it current, instead of re-deriving knowledge per query — is due to
  Andrej Karpathy.
  https://gist.github.com/karpathy/442a6bf555914893e9891c11519de94f

- The skill set, directory schema, and citation grammar adopt structure from
  kfchou/wiki-skills (MIT, Copyright (c) 2026 kfchou).
  https://github.com/kfchou/wiki-skills

- The git-checkpoint codebase-sync pattern adapts ideas from Yiyi Sun / yysun
  (git-wiki, MIT, Copyright (c) 2025 Yiyi Sun).
  https://github.com/yysun/awesome-agent-world

These upstream projects are MIT-licensed; this repository does not vendor their code,
only their publicly documented patterns. Full source-by-source provenance for every
design decision is in SOURCES.md.
